Pareudiastes

); (x) rectrices forming normally-shaped tail (in 

Pareudiastes

, rectrices very short barely protruding beyond uppertail- and undertail-coverts); (xi) leading edge of distalmost primary with narrow white margin (absent in 

Pareudiastes

); (xii) underwing-coverts with white bars (not barred in 

Pareudiastes

); (xiii) bend of wing whitish (no white colouration in 

Pareudiastes

); and (xiv) presence of narrow cutaneous folds on lateral and medial sides of digits I–IV of feet (absent in 

Pareudiastes

).

